result.execSummary:
The deferred prosecution or sentencing agreement(s) on this case were fulfilled, and the charge(s) were dismissed.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Kadesia R Shepherd-Lowe in court with attorney Terese M. Dick.  David T. Malone appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  sdg

The defendant has complied with the Deferred Prosecution Agreement.  On motion of the State, Court ordered case dismissed with prejudice.  Bail to be returned if applicable.

Court ordered Restitution payable to KIM Q in the amount of FOUR HUNDRED AND TWENTY-FIVE DOLLARS converted to a Civil Judgment FORTHWITH.

Defendant Kadesia R Shepherd-Lowe in court with attorney Terese M. Dick.  Brad Alan Vorpahl appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  sdg

Review hearing proceeded on the Record.  Defense advised that Defendant will be with Lad Lake for the next TWO (2) YEARS.  Defendant's income is therefore LIMITED.  Court went off the Record to hold Sidebar.  Hearing continued on the Record.  State is willing to allow Defendant to pay to the HALFWAY point.  The remainder of Restitution will be THREE HUNDRED AND FIVE DOLLARS ($305.00).  Court held colloquy with the Defendant.  Court ordered matter adjourned to Br. 33 for Review.  Review hearing scheduled for November 8, 2016 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Kadesia R Shepherd-Lowe in court with attorney Terese M. Dick.  David T. Malone appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  sdg

Hearing proceeded on the Record.  Defense advised that Restitution is still outstanding.  State did NOT object to an extension.  Defendant brough a payment of TWENTY DOLLARS ($20.00) towards Restitution.  With agreement of parties, Court extends Deferred Prosecution Agreement to next court date.  Case adjourned for final review hearing in Branch 33.  ON MOTION OF THE STATE,  COURT ORDERED JUSTICEPOINT REMOVED.  Review hearing scheduled for August 9, 2016 at 01:30 pm.
JusticePoint DPA Progress Report.  Filed, sdg.

Defendant Kadesia R Shepherd-Lowe in court with attorney Terese M. Dick.  David T. Malone appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  sdg

Defendant is under Doctor's Care.  Defendant advised she could commence Community Service starting 03-18-2016.  Court ordered matter adjourned to Br. 33 for Review.  Review hearing scheduled for May 10, 2016 at 01:30 pm.
JusticePoint DPA Progress Report.  Filed, sdg.

Defendant Kadesia R Shepherd-Lowe in court with attorney Terese M. Dick.  Brad Alan Vorpahl appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  sdg

Hearing proceeded on the Record.  Defendant has not yet started Community Service or paying restitution.  Court ordered matter adjourned to Br. 33 for Review.  Review hearing scheduled for March 15, 2016 at 01:30 pm.
JusticePoint DPA Progress Report.  Filed, sdg.

Defendant Kadesia R Shepherd-Lowe in court with attorney Terese M. Dick.  Daniel J. Gabler appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  The parties have agreed to a deferred judgment agreement.The defendant was advised of his constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, pled GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionaire/Wiaver of Rights and Addendum to Plea Questionaire received and filed.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty but WITHHELD entry of Judgement of Conviction.  The Court reviewed the Intake Requirement and Further Conditions with the defendant.  The court approved the Deferred Prosecution Agreement and ordered the proceedings transferred to Judge Ashley, Branch 33 for a review hearing.
  Review hearing scheduled for January 12, 2016 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Kadesia R Shepherd-Lowe in court with attorney Terese M. Dick.  Daniel J. Gabler appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  Deferred prosecution agreement hearing scheduled for October 26, 2015 at 08:30 am.
Defendant advised it is a requirement to attend all future court proceedings.  Failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.
Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with Kim Q

Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Protasiewicz, Branch 24.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of right to counsel and complaint given to defendant's attorney.  Defendant plead not guilty.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND QUALIFIES FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION.

Defendant Kadesia R Shepherd-Lowe in court with attorney Brian Christopher Hagner.  Defendant Kadesia R Shepherd-Lowe in custody.  James W. Frisch appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk:  bm
  Request for Substitution of Judge received and filed.  Court consented to substitution against Judge Siefert.  Parties are advised the Clerk of Circuit Court reassigned case pursuant to current court rules to Judge Protasiewicz, Br. 24.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for September 25, 2015 at 08:30 am.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
